  "response_text": "In a bright, tidy living room, a person is partly visible at the right edge, seen from the waist down in pale pink pants and light shoes. They guide a full-size upright vacuum with a blue bag across a tan carpet. The room has a soft, domestic look: a pale blue armchair sits near curtained windows, a beige sofa is behind a wooden coffee table with decorative objects, and shelves and plants fill the background. The upright vacuum is then replaced visually by a compact red handheld vacuum, held out in the person’s hand by its top handle, with its black power cord trailing behind.\n\nA small, fluffy white dog lies on a pale blue upholstered chair or sofa cushion. The red handheld vacuum rests nearby at the left. As the dog moves off the cushion, patches of light-colored hair or debris are left scattered across the fabric. A hand brings the red Dirt Devil hand vac onto the cushion and pushes it steadily over the mess. The compact vacuum has a rounded red body, a top handle, a black front intake opening, small side vents, and a red soft-looking dust bag at the rear. As it passes over the blue fabric, the visible clumps of hair and dirt disappear beneath the nozzle, leaving the surface cleaner.\n\nThe vacuum is then shown upright in close detail with its underside facing forward. A metal-framed opening reveals two cylindrical brush areas inside the head. The view centers on the revolving brush mechanism, with bristles visible behind the gray rollers, highlighting that this handheld cleaner has a brush like a larger upright vacuum.\n\nThe setting changes to the inside of a car. The red hand vac is positioned on a gray car seat where dark crumbs or dirt are scattered along the seat seam. A person in pink clothing holds the vacuum while also using a white hose and narrow attachment. White on-screen text at the lower left reads “Attachments Available.” The hose attachment is aimed into the tight spaces between the car seat and center area, suggesting cleaning in narrow crevices.\n\nThe vacuum is also used on carpeted stairs. The red handheld unit is pressed against a gray stair tread between white vertical banister posts, with a polished wooden rail or stair edge visible at the bottom. A hand holds the top handle as the compact vacuum fits into the stair area, where a full-size vacuum would be harder to maneuver.\n\nThe commercial returns to the living room view. The person again guides the blue upright vacuum over the carpet, then the image shifts back to the red handheld Dirt Devil held at about waist height, visually comparing the small hand vac to the larger upright. The final product display places the red Dirt Devil hand vac on a clean white background. Large red lettering reads “Dirt Devil,” with smaller black text beside it reading “HAND VAC.” The Royal brand name appears below, and the product sits angled to show its red body, rear dust bag, handle, vents, and black front nozzle.",
